reviewText: Even though it's a little predictable, "Seventeen Again" is a great family movie. It was originally aired on Showtime in 2000, and subsequently shown on Disney Channel many times. Anyone who grew up watching Disney Channel in the early 2000s would appreciate watching this or getting it as a nostalgic gift!It's basically about a 12-year-old boy who experiments with chemicals in hopes of finding a way to keep his dog from aging. No one knew the chemicals seeped into bars of soap, and when the boy's divorced grandparents used the soap, they turned--you guessed it--17 again. They enjoyed the benefits of being young again, hung out around the local high school and got dates, and tried to stay away from each other but ended up getting closer than ever. Meanwhile, their granddaughter, who is identical to the 17-year-old version of the grandmother, is having boy troubles of her own.The story is cute and sweet, and the only way you could not enjoy it is if you tried very hard to bash on it. The music is also pretty good too.

reviewText: What if you had the chance to be young again? This is the prospect explored in this film as a teenage girl's grandmother gets that chance, turning her into a lookalike of said granddaughter (hence the roles of Tia and Tamera Mowry) Grandpa also gets his youth back, and the two oldsters explore their youth and learn quite a bit about themselves and how to fix the marriage that had been on the brink of end before they became young. I actually liked this film, and I am sure that there are plenty of old people who would literally jump at the chance to be young, though I certainly wouldn't want to go back to being old (as happens at the end)

reviewText: Anyone who is a fan of Tia & Tamera (from Nickelodean's 'Sister Sister' will love this. And even if you're not, im sure you will enjoy this. Its the story of a young boy (Tahj Mowry who is also a little cutie!) who accidently contaminates his grandparents soap which upon using, causes the two to turn into 17 year olds again.Tamera plays the young grandma, Tia plays Tahj's sister, and an actor named Mark Taylor (who by the way is incredibly gorgeous!) plays the young grandfather.Its funny and also quite romantic.. but perfect for kids or adults. All the songs are done by Shawn Stockman (from BoysIIMen) and they are an excellent addition to the movie.I saw this on tv a few years back and had to order the dvd as it is a fantastic movie! I recommend it to everyone!
summary: Lots of fun to watch! Loved it!!

reviewText: I loved this movie!  Tia and Tamera really pulled off their characters well.  Tahj as an aspiring scientist was great at causing and fixing the damage he created. The actor who played "teen Gene" was very convincing (and handsome) as a young grandpa.  I thought the film did a wonderful job on comparing the attitudes of today's generation to that of the grandparents'.  It showed that doing your life over again, changes because of the wisdom you gain as an adult.

reviewText: How would you react if your brainy little brother accidently created a formula that could make people young again...and some of it rubbed off on your grandparents?  This is a fun movie with a good moral and cool characters.  It IS hard to constantly invision the grandparents as young people, but I had that problem with "Freaky Friday", too.  Some parts may also be iffy for small children, but other then that, this movie is enjoyable and fun to watch when it's on the Disney Channel.  And it's on about every two or three months, so I wouldn't recommend buying the movie.
